A woman on Thursday morning died on the spot after a matatu travelling on the Kendu Bay-Katito road was involved in an accident at Pap Onditi area. According to witnesses who spoke to Citizen Digital, 16 passengers who sustained injuries were rushed to Nyakach sub-county hospital where they were admitted with broken limbs. Five other passengers of the ill-fated matatu were rushed to the Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Hospital (JOOTRH) for specialized treatment. Nyalunya location Chief Kenneth Omondi Mboya, confirming the incident, said the matatu driver was avoiding hitting a motorcyclist. According to Mboya, the boda boda rider however made an abrupt turn on the road thereby forcing the matatu to lose control and veer off the road. He added that the matatu rolled severally leading to the death and many injuries, further stating that it was also apparent that the vehicle was overloadedÂ during the accident. Also Read: Video Of The Day: Guns galore